msgid "# ShortRequestFirst Prefill Scheduling"
msgstr "# ShortRequestFirst 预填充调度"

msgid ""
"ShortRequestFirst reduces head-of-line blocking during prefill by letting "
"short prompts run before long prompts. It is designed for mixed prompt-"
"length traffic where a few long requests can otherwise delay many short "
"ones."
msgstr ""
"ShortRequestFirst "
"通过让短提示词在长提示词之前运行，减少了预填充阶段的队头阻塞。它专为混合提示词长度的流量场景设计，在这种场景下，少数长请求可能会延迟大量短请求。"

msgid "## When to use it"
msgstr "## 何时使用"

msgid "Enable ShortRequestFirst when:"
msgstr "在以下情况下启用 ShortRequestFirst："

msgid ""
"- request lengths are highly skewed\n"
"- short-request TTFT matters more than strict FCFS ordering\n"
"- the prefill node already runs with the recompute scheduler enabled"
msgstr ""
"- 请求长度高度倾斜\n"
"- 短请求的 TTFT 比严格的 FCFS 顺序更重要\n"
"- 预填充节点已启用重计算调度器运行"

msgid ""
"Keep it disabled if the workload is mostly uniform, or if FCFS ordering is "
"more important than short-request latency."
msgstr "如果工作负载基本均匀，或者 FCFS 顺序比短请求延迟更重要，则保持禁用状态。"

msgid "## Configuration"
msgstr "## 配置"

msgid "### Fields"
msgstr "### 字段"

msgid ""
"- `enabled` (bool, default `false`)\n"
"  Turns ShortRequestFirst on or off.\n"
"- `threshold` (int, default `256`)\n"
"  Requests with `num_prompt_tokens <= threshold` are treated as short requests.\n"
"- `long_max_wait_ms` (float, default `0`)\n"
"  Maximum time a long request may wait behind short requests before it can be promoted ahead of them.\n"
"  `0` disables long-request promotion and keeps strict short-request priority."
msgstr ""
"- `enabled`（布尔值，默认 `false`）\n"
"  打开或关闭 ShortRequestFirst。\n"
"- `threshold`（整数，默认 `256`）\n"
"  `num_prompt_tokens <= threshold` 的请求被视为短请求。\n"
"- `long_max_wait_ms`（浮点数，默认 `0`）\n"
"  长请求在短请求之后等待，直到可以被提升到它们之前的最大时间。\n"
"  `0` 禁用长请求提升并保持严格的短请求优先级。"

msgid "## Threshold tuning"
msgstr "## 阈值调优"

msgid ""
"If `threshold` is too low, most requests fall into the `long` lane and the "
"split largely stops helping. If it is too high, most requests fall into the "
"`short` lane and the split also stops helping."
msgstr ""
"如果 `threshold` 太低，大多数请求会落入 `long` 通道，拆分基本失去作用。如果太高，大多数请求会落入 `short` "
"通道，拆分同样失去作用。"

msgid ""
"In practice, `threshold` should sit near the boundary between the short-"
"request main cluster and the long-request tail. The goal is not to pick a "
"fixed midpoint of all request lengths, and not to move the threshold close "
"to the longest requests."
msgstr ""
"在实践中，`threshold` 应位于短请求主集群和长请求尾部之间的边界附近。目标不是选择所有请求长度的固定中点，也不是将阈值移近最长的请求。"

msgid ""
"If you do not yet have a refined traffic model, start with `P70-P85` of "
"prompt length as an engineering baseline and then refine it using the real "
"request-length histogram. For a clear bimodal workload, the threshold "
"usually belongs near the upper edge of the short-request cluster rather than"
" near the longest prompts."
msgstr ""
"如果尚未建立精细的流量模型，可以从提示词长度的 `P70-P85` "
"作为工程基线开始，然后使用真实的请求长度直方图进行细化。对于清晰的双峰工作负载，阈值通常位于短请求集群的上边缘附近，而不是最长的提示词附近。"

msgid ""
"In short: the right threshold is usually the valley between short-request "
"and long-request populations. When detailed distribution modeling is "
"unavailable, `P70-P85` is a practical starting range."
msgstr "简而言之：正确的阈值通常是短请求和长请求群体之间的谷底。当无法进行详细的分布建模时，`P70-P85` 是一个实用的起始范围。"

msgid "## long_max_wait_ms tuning"
msgstr "## long_max_wait_ms 调优"

msgid ""
"`long_max_wait_ms` is a fairness gate, not a throughput-optimization knob. "
"It controls when a long request stops waiting under normal short-first "
"behavior and becomes eligible for anti-starvation promotion."
msgstr ""
"`long_max_wait_ms` 是一个公平性门控，而不是吞吐量优化旋钮。它控制长请求在正常的短优先行为下何时停止等待，并有资格进行反饥饿提升。"

msgid ""
"Tune `threshold` first. If degradation warnings appear frequently, first "
"suspect that `threshold` is too small for the current traffic mix, then "
"consider increasing `long_max_wait_ms`."
msgstr ""
"首先调整 `threshold`。如果频繁出现降级警告，首先怀疑 `threshold` 对于当前流量组合来说太小，然后考虑增加 "
"`long_max_wait_ms`。"

msgid "A practical tuning flow is:"
msgstr "一个实用的调优流程是："

msgid ""
"- start with `long_max_wait_ms = 0` to establish a strict short-first baseline\n"
"- measure the waiting-time distribution of long requests under that baseline\n"
"- define `W_normal` as the normal upper tail of long-request waiting, typically `P90` or `P95`\n"
"- define `W_slo` as the maximum additional queueing delay that your service can tolerate for long requests\n"
"- set `long_max_wait_ms` somewhere inside `[W_normal, W_slo]`"
msgstr ""
"- 从 `long_max_wait_ms = 0` 开始，建立严格的短优先基线\n"
"- 测量该基线下长请求的等待时间分布\n"
"- 将 `W_normal` 定义为长请求等待的正常上尾，通常是 `P90` 或 `P95`\n"
"- 将 `W_slo` 定义为您的服务可以容忍的长请求的最大额外排队延迟\n"
"- 将 `long_max_wait_ms` 设置在 `[W_normal, W_slo]` 区间内"

msgid ""
"Within that interval, bias the value toward `W_slo` if short-request TTFT "
"matters more, or toward `W_normal` if long-request fairness matters more. If"
" `W_normal` is already close to `W_slo`, the main issue is more likely the "
"threshold choice or overall system capacity than the wait parameter itself."
msgstr ""
"在该区间内，如果短请求 TTFT 更重要，则将值偏向 `W_slo`；如果长请求公平性更重要，则偏向 `W_normal`。如果 `W_normal` "
"已经接近 `W_slo`，主要问题更可能是阈值选择或整体系统容量，而不是等待参数本身。"

msgid ""
"Do not size `long_max_wait_ms` from average short-request TTFT. It is "
"usually better anchored to the tail of long-request waiting under strict "
"short-first behavior."
msgstr "不要根据平均短请求 TTFT 来确定 `long_max_wait_ms` 的大小。它通常更好地锚定在严格短优先行为下长请求等待的尾部。"

msgid ""
"In short: `long_max_wait_ms` should be derived from the long-request waiting"
" tail under strict short-first scheduling and bounded by the long-request "
"queueing delay your service can accept. If aged-long promotions happen "
"repeatedly, increase `threshold` first and only then increase "
"`long_max_wait_ms`."
msgstr ""
"简而言之：`long_max_wait_ms` "
"应从严格短优先调度下的长请求等待尾部推导，并以您的服务可以接受的长请求排队延迟为界。如果老化长请求提升反复发生，请先增加 "
"`threshold`，然后再增加 `long_max_wait_ms`。"

msgid "## Scheduling behavior"
msgstr "## 调度行为"

msgid "The waiting queue is split into three lanes:"
msgstr "等待队列被分为三个通道："

msgid ""
"- `immediate`\n"
"  Recovery-style requests such as preempted requests or requests with already computed tokens.\n"
"- `short`\n"
"  Requests whose prompt length is at or below `threshold`.\n"
"- `long`\n"
"  Requests whose prompt length is above `threshold`."
msgstr ""
"- `immediate`\n"
"  恢复型请求，例如被抢占的请求或已计算令牌的请求。\n"
"- `short`\n"
"  提示词长度小于或等于 `threshold` 的请求。\n"
"- `long`\n"
"  提示词长度大于 `threshold` 的请求。"

msgid "Dispatch priority is:"
msgstr "调度优先级为："

msgid "`immediate > aged-long > short > long`"
msgstr "`immediate > aged-long > short > long`"

msgid "That means:"
msgstr "这意味着："

msgid ""
"- immediate requests always win\n"
"- short requests run before ordinary long requests\n"
"- if the oldest long request waits past `long_max_wait_ms`, it can jump ahead of waiting short requests"
msgstr ""
"- 立即请求始终优先\n"
"- 短请求在普通长请求之前运行\n"
"- 如果最旧的长请求等待超过 `long_max_wait_ms`，它可以跳到等待的短请求之前"

msgid "## Degradation warning"
msgstr "## 降级警告"

msgid ""
"If long requests are promoted ahead of waiting short requests for three "
"consecutive dispatches, vLLM Ascend emits a warning. This indicates the "
"feature is drifting toward long-request priority, usually because the "
"threshold is too small for the current traffic mix."
msgstr ""
"如果长请求连续三次调度被提升到等待的短请求之前，vLLM Ascend "
"会发出警告。这表明该功能正在向长请求优先级漂移，通常是因为阈值对于当前流量组合来说太小。"

msgid "When this warning appears:"
msgstr "当出现此警告时："

msgid ""
"- increase `short_request_first_config.threshold`\n"
"- or disable `short_request_first_config.enabled`"
msgstr ""
"- 增加 `short_request_first_config.threshold`\n"
"- 或禁用 `short_request_first_config.enabled`"

msgid ""
"ShortRequestFirst also emits an aggregate stats log every 5 seconds so queue"
" behavior is visible without adding extra configuration."
msgstr "ShortRequestFirst 还会每 5 秒发出一次聚合统计日志，因此无需添加额外配置即可查看队列行为。"

msgid "## Relationship with recompute scheduler"
msgstr "## 与重计算调度器的关系"

msgid ""
"ShortRequestFirst only changes the waiting-queue policy and is wired into "
"the recompute scheduler. With `recompute_scheduler_enable=false`, the normal"
" scheduler path is used and ShortRequestFirst is not activated."
msgstr ""
"ShortRequestFirst 仅更改等待队列策略，并连接到重计算调度器。当 `recompute_scheduler_enable=false` "
"时，将使用正常的调度器路径，ShortRequestFirst 不会被激活。"

msgid "## Minimal examples"
msgstr "## 最小示例"

msgid "Disable it explicitly:"
msgstr "显式禁用它："

msgid ""
"Add `short_request_first_config` to the prefill (P) node's "
"`scheduler_config` in a PD-disaggregated deployment. Because "
"ShortRequestFirst is wired through the recompute scheduler, keep "
"`recompute_scheduler_enable=true` in the same P-node configuration:"
msgstr ""
"在 PD 分离部署中，将 `short_request_first_config` 添加到预填充（P）节点的 `scheduler_config` "
"中。由于 ShortRequestFirst 通过重计算调度器连接，请在同一 P 节点配置中保持 "
"`recompute_scheduler_enable=true`："
